The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 LOOSE CHANGE

 ICICI Prudential Life Insurance, in association with Bank of India, has launched HomeAssure, a mortgage reducing term assurance, which will cover the outstanding loan amount of Bank of India?s Star Home Loan customers in the event of his or her unfortunate demise. The product includes features like loan on the premium amount, higher non-medical limit and a discounted rate for young borrowers in a joint account.

 The credit and debit cardholders of HDFC Bank can now get foreign exchange currency while travelling abroad with its newly launched ?Forex on swipe? scheme. This facility can be availed of at its terminals in select branches and is currently available in Mumbai, Delhi, Chennai, Pune, Calcutta, Bangalore, Hyderabad, Chandigarh, Ahmedabad and Agra. Apart from foreign exchange, travellers? cheques and foreign demand drafts, cardholders can also get a credit period if they use their credit card.

 ICICI Lombard General Insurance has unveiled 10K Tax Saver Health, a fixed premium health insurance plan at a cost of Rs 10,000, which is totally deductible from total income under section 80D. The plan is only available online at www.icicilombard.com with online payment options of credit card and Internet banking.




